@startuml signal_flow_ambient_lighting
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

title Level 3: Ambient Lighting Signal Flow\n(IVI → Gateway → BCM → Gateway → IVI/CLU)

participant "User" as User #FFE6E6
participant "IVI\n(CAN-HS #2)" as IVI #6699FF
participant "HVAC\n(CAN-HS #2)" as HVAC #FFCCFF
participant "Gateway\n(CGW)" as GW #FFCC66
participant "BCM\n(CAN-LS)" as BCM #99FF99
participant "Ambient Sensor" as SENSOR #FFFFCC
participant "LED Drivers" as LED #CCCCCC
participant "CLU\n(CAN-HS #2)" as CLU #6699FF

== User Selects Theme ==

User -> IVI : Select "SPORT" theme\n(Red, 80% brightness)
activate IVI

IVI -> IVI : Prepare IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)
note right of IVI
    **Message**: IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)
    **Signals**:
    • Ambient_Light_R = 255 (Red)
    • Ambient_Light_G = 0
    • Ambient_Light_B = 0
    • Brightness = 80 (80%)
    • Theme_Package = 0 (SPORT)
    • AliveCounter = N
    • Checksum = CRC
    **Cycle**: 100ms
    **Network**: CAN-HS #2
end note

IVI -> GW : IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)\n[CAN-HS #2, 100ms]
deactivate IVI

== Gateway Routing (Rule R011) ==

activate GW
GW -> GW : Validate CRC & AliveCounter
note right of GW
    **Routing Rule R011**:
    • Source: CAN-HS #2
    • Dest: CAN-LS
    • Priority: Low
    • Latency: <5ms
    • Filter: CRC check
end note

GW -> GW : Route to CAN-LS
GW -> BCM : IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)\n[CAN-LS, routed]
deactivate GW

== BCM Processing ==

activate BCM
BCM -> BCM : Parse RGB, Brightness, Theme
BCM -> BCM : Apply theme profile\n(SPORT = Red)

BCM -> LED : Set RGB(255, 0, 0)\nBrightness 80%
activate LED
LED -> LED : PWM control\n(Red LEDs at 80%)
LED --> BCM : Actual RGB output
deactivate LED

BCM -> BCM : Prepare BCM_LightControl (0x520)
note right of BCM
    **Message**: BCM_LightControl (0x520)
    **Signals**:
    • Headlight_Status = 2 (LOW_BEAM)
    • Ambient_Light_Active = 1 (ACTIVE)
    • Ambient_R_Actual = 255
    • Ambient_G_Actual = 0
    • Ambient_B_Actual = 0
    **Cycle**: 100ms
    **Network**: CAN-LS
end note

BCM -> GW : BCM_LightControl (0x520)\n[CAN-LS, 100ms]
deactivate BCM

== Gateway Routing (Rule R021) ==

activate GW
GW -> GW : Route to CAN-HS #2
note right of GW
    **Routing Rule R021**:
    • Source: CAN-LS
    • Dest: CAN-HS #2
    • Targets: IVI, CLU
    • Priority: Low
    • Latency: <5ms
end note

GW -> IVI : BCM_LightControl (0x520)\n[CAN-HS #2, routed]
GW -> CLU : BCM_LightControl (0x520)\n[CAN-HS #2, routed]
deactivate GW

== Display Feedback ==

activate IVI
IVI -> IVI : Parse Ambient_RGB_Actual
IVI -> User : Display "Ambient Light:\nSPORT (Red, 80%)\n✓ Active"
deactivate IVI

activate CLU
CLU -> CLU : Parse Ambient_Light_Active
CLU -> User : Show ambient light icon\n(Active indicator)
deactivate CLU

== Timing Diagram ==

note over User, CLU
    **Total Latency**: ~10-15ms
    • IVI processing: 1-2ms
    • Gateway routing (R011): 3-5ms
    • BCM processing: 2-3ms
    • LED control: 1-2ms
    • Gateway routing (R021): 3-5ms
    • Display update: 1-2ms
end note

== Continuous Monitoring (100ms cycle) ==

loop Every 100ms
    IVI -> GW : IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)\n[AliveCounter++]
    GW -> BCM : Route to CAN-LS
    BCM -> LED : Maintain RGB(255, 0, 0)
    BCM -> GW : BCM_LightControl (0x520)
    GW -> IVI : Route to CAN-HS #2
    GW -> CLU : Route to CAN-HS #2
end

== User Changes Theme ==

User -> IVI : Select "COMFORT" theme\n(Blue, 60% brightness)
activate IVI

IVI -> IVI : Update IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)
note right of IVI
    **Updated Signals**:
    • Ambient_Light_R = 0
    • Ambient_Light_G = 100
    • Ambient_Light_B = 255 (Blue)
    • Brightness = 60 (60%)
    • Theme_Package = 1 (COMFORT)
end note

IVI -> GW : IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)\n[Updated]
deactivate IVI

activate GW
GW -> BCM : Route to CAN-LS
deactivate GW

activate BCM
BCM -> LED : Set RGB(0, 100, 255)\nBrightness 60%
activate LED
LED -> LED : PWM control\n(Blue LEDs at 60%)
LED --> BCM : Actual RGB output
deactivate LED

BCM -> GW : BCM_LightControl (0x520)\n[Updated]
deactivate BCM

activate GW
GW -> IVI : Route to CAN-HS #2
GW -> CLU : Route to CAN-HS #2
deactivate GW

activate IVI
IVI -> User : Display "Ambient Light:\nCOMFORT (Blue, 60%)\n✓ Active"
deactivate IVI

== Error Handling ==

User -> IVI : Select invalid theme (99)
activate IVI
IVI -> IVI : Validate theme range (0-10)
IVI -> User : Error: "Invalid theme\nPlease select 0-10"
deactivate IVI

note over IVI, BCM
    **Error Scenarios**:
    1. CRC error → Gateway discards message
    2. AliveCounter timeout → BCM uses last valid value
    3. LED driver fault → BCM reports error in BCM_LightControl
    4. Gateway routing failure → Timeout detection (3x cycle time)
end note

== ⭐ Auto Brightness Control (Ambient Light Sensor) ==

SENSOR -> BCM : Ambient light level\n(Analog voltage)
activate BCM
BCM -> BCM : Convert to percentage\n(0-100%)

BCM -> BCM : Prepare BCM_SensorStatus (0x520)
note right of BCM
    **Message**: BCM_SensorStatus (0x520)
    **Signals**:
    • Ambient_Light_Level = 30 (30% - Dark)
    • Rain_Sensor_Level = 0
    • Wiper_Status = 0 (OFF)
    • Headlight_Auto_Status = 1 (ON)
    **Cycle**: 200ms
    **Network**: CAN-LS
end note

BCM -> GW : BCM_SensorStatus (0x520)\n[CAN-LS, 200ms]
deactivate BCM

activate GW
GW -> GW : Route to CAN-HS #2
GW -> IVI : BCM_SensorStatus (0x520)\n[CAN-HS #2, routed]
deactivate GW

activate IVI
IVI -> IVI : Ambient_Light_Level = 30%\n(Dark environment)
IVI -> IVI : Auto-increase brightness\n60% → 90%

IVI -> IVI : Update IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)
note right of IVI
    **Auto-Adjusted**:
    • Brightness = 90 (auto-increased)
    • Auto_Mode = 1 (ENABLED)
end note

IVI -> GW : IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)\n[Updated brightness]
deactivate IVI

activate GW
GW -> BCM : Route to CAN-LS
deactivate GW

activate BCM
BCM -> LED : Set brightness 90%\n(Auto-adjusted)
activate LED
LED -> LED : PWM control at 90%
deactivate LED
BCM -> User : Brighter ambient light\n(Dark environment)
deactivate BCM

== ⭐ Temperature-Linked Lighting (HVAC Integration) ==

HVAC -> HVAC : Read cabin temperature
activate HVAC
HVAC -> HVAC : Prepare HVAC_Status (0x260)
note right of HVAC
    **Message**: HVAC_Status (0x260)
    **Signals**:
    • Cabin_Temperature = 28 (28°C - Warm)
    • Target_Temperature = 22
    • HVAC_Mode = 2 (COOLING)
    • Fan_Speed = 5
    **Cycle**: 200ms
    **Network**: CAN-HS #2
end note

HVAC -> GW : HVAC_Status (0x260)\n[CAN-HS #2, 200ms]
deactivate HVAC

activate GW
GW -> IVI : HVAC_Status (0x260)\n[Routed]
deactivate GW

activate IVI
IVI -> IVI : Cabin_Temp = 28°C (Warm)\n→ Shift color to COOL tone

IVI -> IVI : Update IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)
note right of IVI
    **Temp-Linked Color**:
    • Ambient_Light_R = 0
    • Ambient_Light_G = 150
    • Ambient_Light_B = 255 (Cool Blue)
    • Temp_Linked_Mode = 1 (ENABLED)
end note

IVI -> GW : IVI_AmbientLight (0x400)\n[Temp-adjusted color]
deactivate IVI

activate GW
GW -> BCM : Route to CAN-LS
deactivate GW

activate BCM
BCM -> LED : Set RGB(0, 150, 255)\n(Cool blue for warm cabin)
activate LED
LED -> User : Cool blue ambient light\n(Visual cooling effect)
deactivate LED
deactivate BCM

note over User, CLU
    **Auto Lighting Features (REQ_005, REQ_051)**:

    1. Ambient Light Sensor (REQ_051):
       • BCM senses environment (0-100%)
       • IVI auto-adjusts brightness
       • Dark → Brighter, Bright → Dimmer

    2. Temperature Linking (REQ_005):
       • HVAC reports cabin temp
       • IVI adjusts color tone
       • Warm cabin → Cool colors (blue)
       • Cold cabin → Warm colors (red/orange)

    **Accuracy**: <5% error
    **Response Time**: <500ms
end note

@enduml
